<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Your One-Time Password (OTP)</title>
    <style>
      body {
        background-color: #f5f7fa;
        font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 40px auto;
        background-color: #ffffff;
        padding: 40px;
        box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
        text-align: center;
        border-radius: 8px;
      }
      h2 {
        color: #333333;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
      }
      p {
        font-size: 16px;
        color: #555555;
        line-height: 1.5;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
      }
      .otp-code {
        font-size: 32px;
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #007bff;
        margin: 30px 0;
        padding: 15px 25px;
        background-color: #e6f2ff;
        border-radius: 8px;
        display: inline-block; /* To make padding and background work */
        letter-spacing: 2px; /* For better readability of the code */
      }
      .small {
        font-size: 13px;
        color: #999999;
        margin-top: 20px;
      }
      .footer {
        margin-top: 30px;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: #777777;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Your One-Time Password (OTP)</h2>
      <p>Dear User,</p>
      <p>
        You have requested a One-Time Password (OTP) to verify your identity. Please use the
        following code to complete your action:
      </p>
      <p class="otp-code"><%= otp %></p>
      <p>
        This OTP is valid for 2 minutes. Please do not share this code with anyone for your
        security.
      </p>
      <p class="small">
        If you did not request this OTP, please ignore this email. Your account remains secure.
      </p>
      <p class="footer">Thank you,<br />Awning Company</p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
